| HistoryText             = Team X was a military black-ops unit established in the 1960s by the joint efforts of the subversive organization known as [[Weapon Plus (Earth-616)|Weapon Plus]] and the [[United States Government (Earth-616)|U.S. Government]]'s [[Central Intelligence Agency (Earth-616)|Central Intelligence Agency]],{{r|History of the Marvel Universe Vol 2 2}} overseen by C.I.A. operative [[Arthur Barrington (Earth-616)|Major Arthur Barrington]].{{r|X-Men Vol 2 5|7}}

Named '''Team X''', as it was composed of [[Homo superior|mutant]] agents, the black-ops squad undertook several missions for the C.I.A., the Weapon Plus Program,{{r|History of the Marvel Universe Vol 2 2}} and, although possibly unwillingly, for the criminal mastermind known as [[Romulus (Earth-616)|Romulus]], who used his personal undercover agents, [[James Howlett (Earth-616)|Logan]] (codenamed: [[Wolverine]]) and [[Victor Creed (Earth-616)|Victor Creed]] (codenamed: [[Sabretooth]]) to carry on his own interests.{{r|Wolverine: Origins #8}} Other team members included C.I.A. operatives [[Christoph Nord (Earth-616)|David North]] (codenamed: [[Maverick]]){{r|X-Men Vol 2 5}} and [[John Wraith (Earth-616)|John Wraith]] (codenamed: [[Kestrel]]),{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 60}} as well as the mysterious [[Mastodon (Elefante) (Earth-616)|Mastodon]] and Wolverine's former love, [[Silver Fox (Canadian) (Earth-616)|Silver Fox]],{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 49}} although likely an imposter hired by either the C.I.A., Weapon Plus or Romulus himself.{{r|Wolverine: Weapon X Files #1}}

Team X operatives also underwent multiple brainwashing sessions, with their memories largely altered or replaced by false ones implanted by the Weapon Plus teams, under the lead of the program's head scientist, [[Truett Hudson (Earth-616)|Professor Thorton]].{{r|Wolverine Vol 7 9}}

In 1963 agents Logan, codenamed ''Emilio Garra'', and Sabretooth, codenamed ''El Tigre'', were on a mission in [[Cuba]] after [[John F. Kennedy (Earth-616)|Kennedy]]'s assassination, where they had been betrayed by Silver Fox.{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 49}} They were later joined by agents Mastodon and Wraith, and together they clashed against Silver Fox, known as ''Zora de Plata''.{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 61}}

Agents Logan, Sabretooth and Wraith were sent on a mission in [[Asia|Southeast Asia]].{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 61}}

Also in 1963{{r|Wolverine: Origins Vol 1 7|8}} Romulus C.I.A. scienticists in [[Dallas]], [[Texas (State)|Texas]], experimenting on Logan with [[Carbonadium]] pills;{{r|Wolverine: Origins #6|7}} The whole squad was sent on Team X's last mission in [[Berlin]], [[Germany]]; they were ordered to save C.I.A. double agent [[Janice Hollenbeck (Earth-616)|Janice Hollenbeck]] and to stole [[Komitet Gosudarstvennoy Bezopasnosti (Earth-616)|K.G.B.]]'s [[Carbonadium Synthesizer]], required by soviet super-soldier [[Arkady Rossovich (Earth-616)|Omega Red]];{{r|X-Men Vol 2 5|7}}{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 60|61}}{{r|Wolverine: Origins #8}} Wraith tried to kill Red with a new weapon, but he survived and Wraith managed to teleport himself away to safety.{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 60|61}} In the following years, Omega Red continuously sought out the Team X members, believing they may know of its whereabouts.{{r|X-Men Vol 2 5|7}}

In 1968, Wolverine was send to kill Soviet's Super-Soldier Cosmonaut [[Epsilon Red (Earth-616)|Epsilon Red]] to keep the Russians from reaching the Moon first. When Sabretooth who fought his way through elite K.G.B., border guards and internal security to deliver an abort mission orders from the very top of the food chain.{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 68}}{{r|Maverick Vol 1 1}}

Several years after the team disbanded, Weapon Plus formed its tenth iteration, the subversive [[Weapon X (Earth-616)|Weapon X Program]], overseen by Professor Thornton and funded by the C.I.A. through the [[United States Department of Agriculture (Earth-616)|U.S. Department of Agriculture]].{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 50}} Thornton successfully contacted or captured the former Team X alumni, who were infused with a serum which mimicked Wolverine's healing factor and received a new layer of memory implants initially through staged scenarios,{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 50}} and later using [[Aldo Ferro (Earth-616)|Aldo Ferro]]'s psychic powers.{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 60|65}}

Later, Wolverine successfully escaped the [[Weapon X Facility]] where he was experimented on in [[Alberta]], [[Canada]],{{r|Marvel Comics Presents #72|84}} while Mastodon retired,{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 61|62}} Wraith was employed by the U.S. Government,{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 60|65}} Sabretooth continued working for Romulus,{{r|Wolverine Vol 3 53|55}} and Silver Fox disappeared,{{r|Wolverine Vol 2 50}} with the only Maverick still working for the Weapon X Program.{{r|Weapon X Vol 2 23}}

